archetypes.name: Limits to Success
archetypes.rationale: The model shows growth in user base and adoption driven by project reputation and software quality, but faces constraints from maintainer time, PR review delays, and developer turnover that limit further growth.

variables.name: Growth Pressure
variables.description: Pressure to continue growing despite constraints
variables.rationale: Needed to complete the balancing loop structure

variables.name: Constraint Awareness
variables.rationale: Missing feedback mechanism to detect constraints

connections.rationale: Larger user base creates more growth pressure

archetypes.name: Tragedy of the Commons
archetypes.rationale: Maintainer time and community capacity appear as shared resources that can be depleted by excessive pull requests, issues, and demands from growing user base without coordination mechanisms.

variables.name: Resource Depletion Rate
variables.description: Rate at which shared resources are consumed
variables.rationale: Missing explicit tracking of resource consumption

variables.name: Coordination Mechanism
variables.description: Processes for managing shared resource usage
variables.rationale: Missing balancing mechanism to prevent overuse

connections.rationale: More PRs consume more maintainer time

archetypes.name: Shifting the Burden
archetypes.rationale: The model suggests potential for quick fixes (like rapid PR merging) that undermine long-term community health and knowledge transfer, but lacks explicit symptom and fundamental solution variables.

variables.name: Symptomatic Solution
variables.description: Quick fixes that address immediate symptoms
variables.rationale: Missing explicit representation of short-term solutions

connections.rationale: Delays create pressure for quick fixes

archetypes.name: Growth and Underinvestment
archetypes.rationale: The model shows growth dynamics but lacks explicit investment variables in community capacity, knowledge management, and infrastructure that could lead to performance degradation as demand increases.

variables.name: Capacity Investment
variables.description: Investment in community capacity and infrastructure

variables.name: Performance Gap
variables.description: Difference between desired and actual performance
variables.rationale: Missing feedback signal for investment needs
